gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Dataset Status_2003.shp was converted from shapefile to ArcInfo coverage and moved to a reference library

This metadata was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit, v 2.6.1) and MP (Metadata Parser, v 2.7.1) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (U.S. Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected.
Ownership is continually updated and edited with the most current information

Bernardin, Lochmueller & Associates received an ESRI ArcGIS 9.2 coverage named "hnf_own" from the Hoosier National Forest in May 2007. ArcGIS 9.2 was used to export the coverage into a shapefile format. The fields "hnf_own_" and "hnf_own_id" were deleted. The data in the field "owner" was replaced from code to text definition where code 620 = private and code 621 = USFS.
